Seung U 승우 양평점  225 Yanggeun ro  Yangpyeong eup  Yangpyeong gun  Gyeonggi do  South Korea We ordered the Rosu Katsu 로스카츠  Cheese Katsu 치즈카츠  and Hire Katsu 히레카츠  forgot to take a close up pic bc i was too hungry    The Cheese Katsu was mine  i wanted to compare the one at Seung U to the one i usually eat at The Basac  Flushing  NY   the one at The Basac is better  both in size of the katsu  taste of the panko  and also the fact that the cheese is slower to harden  The best one at Seung U was probably the Hire Katsu  tenderloin  bc of how soft  butter like  and  tender  the meat was  more fat marbling   The Rosu Katsu  sirloin  was also good but the meat had more thickness and texture  less fat   The Hire and Rosu Katsu went very well with salt wasabi  and their brown sauce was good with all 3 types of katsu  i personally prefer eating katsu with sauce so that I don t get too much of the raw meat flavor   Overall  the food here is delicious  but it s not necessarily a must try  The meat is def high quality  very soft and juicy  none were dry stiff to eat  The katsu coat was freshly fried  very crispy  and I could tell that it was breaded very well bc the coat was thin and it did not separate from the meat       The sides that come with the set  however  seemed to be made with less care  the rice  miso soup  and salad   but that s understandable  The interior was clean and simple but empty  we were the only customers 0   Oh also  they give lightly brewed green tea instead of regular water which I thought was unique  although some ppl like my cousin might not be pleased
